OL,4,Cwrongdoing with convict
OL,6,FGiving evidence from the witness box
OL,7,Fin her own defence, Pegg said she
OL,8,Fjoined the Prison Service after
OL,9,Fworking for the Probation Service for
OL,10,Feight years, because she liked working
OL,11,Fwith people and wanted to "make a
OL,12,Fdifference".
OL,14,FShe told jurors she currently works
OL,15,Ffor a poverty and homeless charity in
OL,16,FWigan, called The Brick, who she had
OL,17,Ftold about her court case and some
OL,18,Fpeople from the charity were attending
OL,19,Fcourt.
